%% Training Operator - Data Flow Diagram
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6

sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User / Pipeline
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Webhook as Validating Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant Operator as Training Operator<br/>Reconciler
    participant DNS as Headless Service<br/>53/UDP DNS
    participant Workers as Worker Pods<br/>Framework-specific/TCP

    Note over User,Workers: Flow 1: Training Job Reconciliation

    User->>K8sAPI: POST PyTorchJob CR<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / kubeconfig
    K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-kubeflow-org-v1-pytorchjob<br/>HTTPS/9443, TLS (self-managed)<br/>Auth: API server client cert
    Webhook-->>K8sAPI: AdmissionReview Response<br/>(Allowed/Denied)
    K8sAPI-->>User: CR Created

    Note over Operator,Workers: Reconcile Loop

    K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch Event (PyTorchJob)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Worker Pods<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Bearer Token
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Headless Services<br/>(per replica for DNS discovery)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicy<br/>(PyTorchJob isolation)
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Create HPA (if elastic)<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    Operator->>K8sAPI: Update Job Status<br/>(replica status + conditions)

    Note over DNS,Workers: Flow 2: Distributed Training Communication

    Workers->>DNS: DNS Lookup<br/>{job}-{type}-{idx}.{ns}.svc<br/>53/UDP plaintext
    DNS-->>Workers: Pod IP addresses
    Workers->>Workers: Gradient Sync / Parameter Exchange<br/>Framework-specific/TCP plaintext<br/>Restricted by NetworkPolicy

    Note over Operator,Workers: Flow 3: Metrics Collection

    participant Prometheus as Prometheus<br/>(openshift-monitoring)
    Prometheus->>Operator: GET /metrics<br/>HTTP/8080 plaintext<br/>Auth: None
    Operator-->>Prometheus: Prometheus metrics
